         <abstract id="aspace_20b9ac6911417aa396b77c4980db061d">This collection encompasses accessions of single letters and small groups of letters and other manuscripts, pertaining to the California Gold Rush, which the library has chosen to group and list as an artificial collection. Letters discuss voyages to the Pacific coast, including journeys through Panama; mining life in California; the inhabitants of California, including Mormons; vigilance committees in San Francisco; and the establishment of a police force in Nevada City, California. Some letters include pictorial letterheads.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_0748c0ccc87caf2e2edea4f660e738f3">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Collection of documents acquired by gift and purchase from various sources. Source information is recorded in the finding aid or on the folders. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
