         <c id="ref10" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Edmunds, A. C. and Cynthia</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1852-1860</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_3e878eaa5e3b46375076b58da1a2de95"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_8078ece1a62d557dd2af52c2c309744c"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_3e878eaa5e3b46375076b58da1a2de95">1</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_e74addf673c217109f7d453c1c2676c5">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letters, signed, from A. C. Edmunds from Downieville, California to his family in Michigan concerning his life in California, the Universalist faith, his work as a missionary preacher to Gold Rush miners, and the temperance movement. With three letters to Cynthia Edmunds from unidentified friends, a poem entitled "My Sister's Grave," and unidentified manuscript poems and speeches.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref12" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Field, Edward G.</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1852-1854</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_202baa43b2fa955deaa2cf9dd5358190"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_47ffd149412ad85077a55c4689c8e4b7"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_202baa43b2fa955deaa2cf9dd5358190">2</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_0a43fce7e52ba94acc51338d5fca866b">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letters, signed, from Sacramento, California, to Field's sister, commenting on raising hogs during the Gold Rush and the high level of immigration to California.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref14" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Field, Henry B.</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1850</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_96d2037dfbe85a3c8f0c81bc82e8d5fc"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_11a8acd466beb88f49f2c6ca46314212"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_96d2037dfbe85a3c8f0c81bc82e8d5fc">3</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_447c3dc6fd0d581b5ec87e14970ad35a">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letters, signed, from San Francisco to a "Mr. Merriman." The letters concern Field's efforts to sell newspapers, become a merchant, and work as a miner. Field gives lengthy descriptions of the process of mining and the life of miners.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref16" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Fox, Peren V.</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1853-1855</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_0696df88bb3c88f36aefc7e309af1ec5"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_1978bb7e1a1463cfe20fea337abc4aff"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_0696df88bb3c88f36aefc7e309af1ec5">4</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_82e4b86d4a23c5187d6be916bcc7e237">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letters, signed, from Mariposa, California to Fox's wife Ida, and a letter to Fox from an E. Leland regarding Leland's employment.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref18" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Hammond, John Henry</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1860</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_573c20bef7196fa64d129e7b0e1f653b"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_49871c5ecfef6f438b7cec30ca1b9e65"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_573c20bef7196fa64d129e7b0e1f653b">5</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_42d05b8b80e869bac6188c30e7494a03">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Typescript copy of a letter from San Francisco to "Mr. and Mrs. Henry Conklin" regarding Hammond's journey to California, especially his travels through Yosemite.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref20" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Hyde, C. C.</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1851</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_563df5eb9c43545856debec0ce9bdf62"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_dc379117f644291619f4feea180b1da5"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_563df5eb9c43545856debec0ce9bdf62">6</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_857174be4162f8763e81506a7e72fbfe">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letters, signed, from San Francisco concerning Hyde's financial and legal struggles, including his efforts to obtain money he is owed by selling Los Angeles gold stock.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref22" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Jones, George Warren</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1859-1861</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_7bef8de6e1c4a58b6f214ac4ca7aff9e"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_13a794aa48f57c12c00435febc89372d"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_7bef8de6e1c4a58b6f214ac4ca7aff9e">7</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_9e9f367e75fabd0dfd8a20d155ee5365">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Seventeen autograph letters, signed, to Jones' father from a steamship, Crescent City, California, and Smith River Valley, California. Letters concern mining, lumber, an 1860 massacre at Carson Valley of white people by Native Americans, and Indian rain dances.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="aspace_157a5e1e93147f6dcc1daca04aca2b5b" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Kendall, George A.</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">[1850?] April 10</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_61ddd0291914f1f8c75771832bd2b9b9"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_6ddfef8f639062c570afcbbffd0324ff"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_61ddd0291914f1f8c75771832bd2b9b9">7a</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_7b8fcff881560cc6f1ca18e52eeda5dc">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letter, signed, to his brother-in-law, Benjamin Moors Stanley, describing his life as a miner in Diamond Springs, California, particularly his mining work and social interactions.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref24" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Kerr family</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1850-1853</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_7ec62ea0052d4c22b219116425d6227d"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_91ccd5be8669560719bf317ffdf3e4fb"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_7ec62ea0052d4c22b219116425d6227d">8</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_5ddb5ef7d0739dbf4696550727988052">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph letters, signed, to James and Hetty Ann Kerr from members of the Kerr-Johnston family. Letters describe the Gold Rush, Fort Laramie, Fort Kearney, crossing the plains to California, and mining life.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref26" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Latimer, L. D.</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1877</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_362d812b65bd603755d84e18bbe0821d"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_da79eb4468e23e9c09ff13c80ea9fe5d"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_362d812b65bd603755d84e18bbe0821d">9</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_a09265236474966d94fd4f85bad1fd52">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Autograph statement, signed, by Latimer as U.S. Attorney, District of California, San Francisco, that no indictment has been found against any persons for collecting the Foreign Miners License Tax.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
         <c id="ref28" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Leibee, Daniel</unittitle>
               <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1850-1866</unitdate>
               <container containerid="39002104796165"
                          id="aspace_458bd8c9761a850a1c635b1d2226f0c0"
                          label="Mixed Materials"
                          localtype="box">1</container>
               <container id="aspace_969ba5d65d09a91776611992da75cb02"
                          localtype="folder"
                          parent="aspace_458bd8c9761a850a1c635b1d2226f0c0">10</container>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_2cfcc616cf07816574cb47302b326aa0">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
